		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 29th 6:52 AM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1112058294560715935&num=15&post=1&replyto=1112097094599023408"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1112097094599023408></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9740 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">czaemon wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><br>what mobs enrage earlier?&nbsp;&nbsp;I've done just about every zone in the game, and *never* seen one.  mobs that appear to enrage later do so because a substantial amount of damage was dealt before the next serverside tick.<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Hmmm... Don't quote me on this, but I'm reasonably sure I've seen mobs enrage as early as 15%<br><br>Admittedly, the last time I can think of mob enraging that early was like back in ToV, so I could just be remembering wrong.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />its also fairly important for tanks to turn off autoattack prematurely in highend situations.  Even in tipt -- a single group zone -- the lag between when you hit autoattack off and when the server receives it can result in 8k damage. <hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Agree 100%. What I was trying to get across is that the only one who needs to worry about that is the tank. When I'm tanking I assess whether I need to just turn off autoattack for the last part of the battle or not (In my case, I can agro just fine while barehanded, so it's pretty unimportant). I interpreted what you said as *all* melee turn off autoattack at 10%. While there may certainly be some encounters where you'll do that just to be safe, the vast majority of the time, assuming your tank is doing his job right, and the rest of the melees are positioned correctly, all that'll do is make the kill take longer. I've seen fights fail, not becuase the tank died, or agro got lost, but simply because folks paniced on enrage and all did the &quot;automatic&quot; act of turning off their attacks when enrage hit slowing dps to a crawl in a situation where healer mana was just that tight. You can't rely on nukes alone to finish off that last 10%, and sometimes the extra time spent waiting for enrage to end is just enough to cost you the fight.<br><br>It's just a pet peeve of mine to see enrage go off and see *everyone* stop attacking (it's *really* noticable!). I understand that there are exceptions to every rule, but in my book if you are behind the mob, you keep attacking when enrage goes off.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
