		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 29th 10:51 AM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1112058294560715935&num=15&post=1&replyto=1112111463631923036"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1112111463631923036></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=159622"><span id=Scholar>Wayen</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />205 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.14]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Wayen&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>If the mob is capable of enrage, the mob will become enraged somewhere between 9% and 10% health left.&nbsp;&nbsp;I want to say that it occurs at 9.5%, but since my UI only show whole numbers, it happens sometime after the mob changes from 10% to 9%, but not right at that moment.<br><br>When a mob is enraged, it will RIPOSTE ALL FRONTAL MELEE ATTACKS.  A riposte is the mob will get a successful counterattack for each swing someone takes at it form the front.  So imagine a tank with two fast weapons and hasted, EACH time that tank swings (hit or miss) the mob will land a successful attack on the tank.  Couple notes about enrage and riposte.  The ripostes are in addition to the mobs normal attacks.  Also, ripostes cannot be slowed since they are a function of someone attacking it.<br><br>Enrage lasts for a set period of time, like 15 secs.  There are messages &quot;The mob has become ENRAGED&quot; and &quot;The mob is no longer enraged&quot;.  The best thing to do is to turn off auto-attack on anyone attacking from the front.  Those behind the mob can continue to attack, as long as the mob does not turn around.  If the mob is enraged and turns around, it will riposte all those attacks.  So during enrage the tank either needs to have built up enough aggro to keep the mob facing at him, or he needs to do anything to keep aggro.<br><br>Any melee that attacks a mob from the front during enrage deserves to die.  Do not expect a healer to heal someone taking damage from an enraged mob.  The healers just can compete with the damage.<br><br>Enrage does nothing to spells and ranged attacks.  Please note that they tank has attack off at this point, so casters if already high on the aggro list may pass the tank so be careful.  If you have everything setup correctly, you can often kill the mob with rear attacks and spells before enrage ends.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
